<subSubSection id="C308656BFFE2FFA4FF781FCD83E3F974" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BAD36E0FFE2FFA4FF781FCD8213F98C" blockId="1.[151,1436,1486,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FF781FCD80F7FA27" bold="true" box="[199,483,1486,1510]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" reason="1">Distribution and biology.</emphasis>
Only known from the Kangding area of China's 
<collectingRegion id="49D6F802FFE2FFA4FC531FCD85B1FA24" box="[1004,1189,1486,1509]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Sichuan province</collectingRegion>
on the east edge of the Tibetan plateau. All specimens were collected in mid April at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CEA9B05FFE2FFA4FC011FF28506F9C9" box="[958,1042,1521,1544]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="3200.0">3200 m</quantity>
; both males and females are strongly attracted to light even during periods of snowfall but appear to have a local distribution, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D63FFE2FFA4FB021C178472F9EA" authorityName="Gyulai &amp; Ronkay &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2011" box="[1213,1382,1556,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Cerastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspira">
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FB021C178472F9EA" box="[1213,1382,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Cerastis aspira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was discovered only in the Kangding Valley near Zheduo Pass.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAD36E0FFE2FFA4FF781C5A83E3F974" blockId="1.[151,1436,1486,1717]" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">
The new species was uncommon in the shrubby transition between the mountain primary mixed forests and alpine grassland zones. It flies with other early spring moths such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D63FFE2FFA4FCFA1C7F85CBF952" authority="(Warren, 1911)" baseAuthorityName="Warren" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[837,1247,1660,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripalpis">
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FCFA1C7F8526F952" box="[837,1074,1660,1683]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Hyalobole nigripalpis</emphasis>
(Warren, 1911)
</taxonomicName>
or overwintering 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D63FFE2FFA4FF281C9D83E7F974" authority="Hreblay &amp; Ronkay, 1995" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; Ronkay" authorityYear="1995" box="[151,755,1694,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Dasypolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Dasypolia">
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FF281C9D8011F974" box="[151,261,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Dasypolia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FEAB1C9D8095F974" box="[276,385,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">Dasypolia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B966EAF2FFE2FFA4FE2E1C9D80CAF974" box="[401,478,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="47">bicolor</emphasis>
Hreblay &amp; Ronkay, 1995
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
